description.narrative: (Uganda): .Advocacy for Better Health will support advocacy efforts, targeting a range of Family Planning, MCH, Nutrition and WASH and HIV issues in 35 districts with funds from Global Health Program and PEPFAR accounts. In FY 2018, the activity will support local civil society engagement to: 1) increase citizens' demand for quality services; 2) hold government accountable for its commitment to transparency, and accountability in service delivery; 3) decrease stigma and discrimination; and 4) promote sustainability of efforts for improved the quality and availability of essential health, and HIV services. By strengthening citizens' voices through civil society organizations, the activity will promote country ownership of social sector reforms, accountability, rights based services and drive country ownership at all levels to sustain community feedback, improve quality of services and utilization of data to inform programming. .. .. .
